      <p>If you've ever tried to explain BAH, BAS, a PCS move, or a deployment LES to a generalist loan officer, you already know the problem. The way the Navy pays you doesn't fit the box most lenders use. Tax-free allowances get ignored. Frequent moves get read as instability. A veteran's hard-earned <strong style="color:var(--cream)">VA loan entitlement</strong> gets underused because the lender never specialized in it.</p>
      <p>Our navy mortgage programs start from a different place: we already understand how sailors earn, where the income lives on your paperwork, and how to document every dollar correctly. Whether you're active-duty at a homeport like Norfolk or San Diego, a Guard or Reserve sailor balancing a civilian job with drill pay, or an Navy veteran finally putting down roots, we build the file around your real military compensation — and around the VA benefit you earned through service.</p>
      <p>The result is simple: more of your income counted, fewer surprises in underwriting, and a same-day pre-approval letter you can hand to a real estate agent with confidence.</p>
